<task id="creating-dita-map">
  <title>Creating a Map</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>DITA<indexterm>Maps<indexterm>Create map</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>DITA<indexterm>Maps<indexterm>Create subject
          scheme</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>To create a <xref keyref="glossentry_ditamap"><term>DITA map</term></xref>, <xref
          keyref="glossentry_subject-scheme-map"><term>subject scheme map</term></xref>, <xref
          keyref="glossentry_bookmap"><term>bookmap</term></xref>, or other types of <term>DITA
          maps</term>, follow these steps:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Use the <xref href="new-dialog-sa.dita#new-dialog-sa" product="author editor"
              ><uicontrol>New Document</uicontrol> wizard</xref><xref
            href="new-dialog-eclipse.dita#new-dialog-eclipse" product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"
              ><uicontrol>New Document</uicontrol> wizard</xref> to start creating your map.</cmd>
        <info>
          <note type="tip">If you want the <term>map</term> to be a submap, you can create it the
            same way by right-clicking the place in the current map where you want to add it (in the
              <xref href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
                Manager</uicontrol></xref>) and selecting <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> from the
              <uicontrol>Append Child</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>Insert Before</uicontrol>, or
              <uicontrol>Insert After</uicontrol> submenu.</note>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select one of the <uicontrol>DITA Map</uicontrol> templates from the
            <uicontrol>Framework templates</uicontrol> folder.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol product="author editor">Create</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="authorEclipse editorEclipse">Next</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph product="author editor">Select whether you want to open the map in the <xref
              href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
                Manager</uicontrol></xref> or the <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol></ph><ph
            product="authorEclipse editorEclipse">Select a parent folder and the file name and click
              <uicontrol>Finish</uicontrol></ph>.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph product="author editor">Save the map using the <uicontrol><image
                href="../img/Save16.png" id="image_d1d_mmq_sr"/>Save</uicontrol> button on the
            toolbar of the <xref href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA
                Maps Manager</uicontrol> view</xref></ph><ph product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"
            >Save the map after opening it in the <xref
              href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
                Manager</uicontrol></xref> or the Editor</ph>.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
